webpackJsonp([88485353069668],{563:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/rewferguson.com/img/Weather-Lamp/sketch.jpg" alt="weatherLamp sketch"></p>',frontmatter:{title:"sketch"}},projectInfo:{edges:[{node:{name:"Weather Lamp",folder:"weather-lamp",status:2,image:"https://s3.amazonaws.com/rewferguson.com/img/Weather-Lamp/header.svg",description:"I picked an office with no windows, so I’m stuck with artificial light only while I work. I’d like some ambient light provided with RGB LEDs that change their color temperature based on the local weather outside. I’m sure there are lamps that do this, but I would like the light more integrated into my work area. Not one single spot of colored light, but an overall ambient glow. I figure to get this effect I would have to build something myself.",tags:["processing"],github:null,link:null}}]},currentProject:{edges:[{node:{frontmatter:{title:"sketch",date:null},fields:{slug:"/projects/weather-lamp/2015-03-07-sketch/"},excerpt:"",html:'<p><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/rewferguson.com/img/Weather-Lamp/sketch.jpg" alt="weatherLamp sketch"></p>'}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Working with Arduino Pro Mini",date:null},fields:{slug:"/projects/weather-lamp/2015-05-08-working-with-arduino-pro-mini/"},excerpt:"",html:'<p><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/rewferguson.com/img/Weather-Lamp/IMG_1175.jpg" alt="Arduino Pro Mini"></p>'}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Averaging the sky color from a photo",date:null},fields:{slug:"/projects/weather-lamp/2015-05-04-averaging-the-sky-color-from-a-photo/"},excerpt:"In processing I can grab an image of the sky from one of the webcams around Austin and load the pixels in to an array. Its then easy to…",html:'<p>In processing I can grab an image of the sky from one of the webcams around Austin and load the pixels in to an array.</p>\n<p><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/rewferguson.com/img/Weather-Lamp/KXAN02.jpg" alt="webcam image"></p>\n<p>Its then easy to average out the sky pixels to get one rgb value.</p>\n<p><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/rewferguson.com/img/Weather-Lamp/output.png" alt="weather lamp processing output"></p>\n<p>This doesn’t really make a pleasing lamp though.  The color temperature is just way too blue.  I’ll have to find another way of turning an image of the sky into a pleasing lamp color.</p>'}}]}},pathContext:{slug:"/projects/weather-lamp/2015-03-07-sketch/",folder:"/weather-lamp/",folderName:"weather-lamp"}}}});
